<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102728485951272></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102728485951272><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102728485951272>RE: Bard Anew</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102728485951272#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=174788><span id= >Perotinus</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>5 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jul 21st 5:06 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The first significant quests you should do are the Songweaver Quests.<br><br>The armor quests are listed as lvls 5-8 but most of the items you need will more than likely be on EC vendors to save you time.&nbsp;&nbsp;It has slightly lower AC than banded and lots of great modifiers.  I did this at lvl 18 and I'm not giving it up until I get my lambent.<br><br>(One note on the armor: You collect the items and make them in a forge, but you don't need to have any smithing skills.)<br><br>Once you've done the armor, you're offered a quest where you turn in beads from three named orcs in EC.  This is for a good lowbie sword.<br><br>Here's the catch: To get the breastplate for the armor, you need to get two items from wisps which can't be hit with non-magical weapons.  Therefore, you might try to see if you can do the Songweaver Sword quest first.<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Perotinus Forte<br>- Bard of the 20th Song<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
