	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think that many Bards over estimate the drawbacks to a song wearing off.&nbsp;&nbsp;I typically weave five songs.  At level 14 they're:<br><br>Chant of Battle<br>Chords of Dissonance<br>Hymn of Restoration<br>Jonathan's Whistling Warsong<br>Anthem De Arms<br><br>The over all effect of having three out of the five always active far out weighs the short time you go without two of the effects.  This style of weaving allows me to solo blues and whites with little to no downtime (better than 75% health after battle), solo whites and yellows with reasonable downtime(at lest 50% health after battle), and in group with a couple tanks, a shammie/druid, and a couple casters you can fill in all the gaps and ensure nearly no downtime.<br><br>-Caserith<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
